OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/6
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCThe BBC rediscovers the case
OL,4,Cfor the BBC
OL,5,
OL,6,FAndy Burnham's accession as Prime
OL,7,FMinister might signal a move away from
OL,8,Fan acceptance of the primacy of the
OL,9,Ffree market. He appears to be prepared
OL,10,Fto challenge the consensus in
OL,11,Fmainstream politics since the 1980s.
OL,13,FLet's see what this means in practice.
OL,15,FBut it certainly makes it harder to
OL,16,Fargue for anyone who wants to scale
OL,17,Fdown or commercialise the BBC to gain
OL,18,Fthe ear of the government.
OL,20,FSupporters ` including critical friends
OL,21,F` should speak up.
OL,23,EPub: 19-Jul-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
